reviews.text: Pizza is fresh and well baked. could use more crispiness on the crust it the pizza was left a bit longer in the oven. Patron is too strict though. We wanted to sit inside for airconditioning but patron wouldn't let us because we were wearing flip flops despite the restaurant being empty at 3pm on a Sunday afternoon.
Good food, great service

We came here for a group dinner after a workshop meeting, place is pack, we start with some vegetables appetizer then i pick the salmon steak with manggo sauce as the main menu. The salmon steak is excellent. Start the dinner with a carlsberg and close it with a whute wine.
One of my favourite semi buffet lunch places. Excellent service, wide selection of food, truly Italian. I come back every week

Semi buffet lunch is excellent here. You may either choose with or without main course.

Appretizer includes salard, ham, soup, cold cut ... unlimited offer  .

Recommended to share a main course with your lunchmate =)

result.name: DiVino Patio

reviews.text:
We had a delightful time at DiVino for my brother's wedding reception! It was a perfect blend of outdoors and indoors considering we were there for a while and it rained for maybe 20 minutes.

The staff were attentive, but not overly present. They prepared the space and food as requested, and made changes as needed.

The food was delicious, both the salad and charcuterie buffet, and the meal served at our tables.

I would definitely recommend enjoying DiVino Patio!

Value for money and healthy buffet lunch at $178 including soup, salad and cold cuts with some seafood buffet, drink and ice cream. Must tries are the cheese with honey and the smoked Parma ham. Balsamic dressing used good quality olive oil and balsamic vinegar. Waiters were attentive with changing plates and serving water, a rarity in HK.
Very kind staff with the intention of a good stay. The food was ok, not seasoned enough for my taste. Easy to pay since they already added the tip for 10%.

I had the eggplant parmigiana. I’ve had many eggplant parmigiana in my life and this was the most unique and it really worked. Good location. Excellent service and very authentic Italian food.  Prices are in line with everything else in HK... I think it’s high, but it’s the norm around here.
Nice weekday lunch. Good value. Nice to sit outside if there are no smokers around.
